
Overview of adv lightly

The adv lightly has 7 senses (first 5 from tagged texts)
                                         
1. (4) lightly -- (without good reason; "one cannot say such things lightly")
2. (2) lightly, light -- (with few burdens; "experienced travellers travel light")
3. (2) lightly, softly, gently -- (with little weight or force; "she kissed him lightly on the forehead")
4. (2) lightly -- (indulging with temperance; "we eat lightly in the morning")
5. (2) lightly -- (with indifference or without dejection; "he took it lightly")
6. thinly, lightly -- (in a small quantity or extent; "spread the margarine thinly over the meat"; "apply paint lightly")
7. lightly -- (to a slight degree; "her speech is only lightly accented")
